intellectual property
    any unique product of human creation
    encourages speculative work

patent
    legal protection of inventions
    exclusive right to the invention
    patentable, novel, non-obvious, useful/utility

copyright
    reproduction
    distribution
    public display
    public performance
    production of derivative works

fair use
    sometimes legal to reproduce copyrighted work without permission
    purpose and nature of work, amount copied, affect on market